-- Man Group Assets Under Management Fell 2.3% to $38.5 Billion Last Quarter
-- Christiane Lenzner
-- 2010-07-08T06:02:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-08/man-group-assets-under-management-fell-2-3-to-38-5-billion-last-quarter.html

          
          
             Man Group Plc, which is buying hedge-
fund rival GLG Partners Inc., said assets under management
declined to $38.5 billion in the quarter ended June 30 from
$39.4 billion on March 31, the London-based firm said in a
statement today.  
          
          


  


        